WEBVTT



00:00:00.544 --> 00:00:09.952
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons. This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:19.968
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way and I'm confident they'll do the same for you. So get ready to be challenged.

00:00:19.488 --> 00:00:28.224
be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the Church.

00:00:28.864 --> 00:00:31.488
supposing him to be the gardener.

00:00:31.968 --> 00:00:34.176
The sermon by Charles Spurgeon,

00:00:34.464 --> 00:00:36.032
Part three.

00:00:36.864 --> 00:00:39.424
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:00:39.680 --> 00:00:41.984
John's gospel chapter 20

00:00:42.016 --> 00:00:43.456
Verse 15:

00:00:44.768 --> 00:00:46.112
Thirdly,

00:00:45.984 --> 00:00:50.560
I have found in this supposition supposing him to be the gardener,

00:00:50.496 --> 00:00:51.904
A relief

00:00:51.808 --> 00:00:54.304
From crushing responsibility.

00:00:55.712 --> 00:00:58.944
One has a work given him a God to do.

00:00:59.136 --> 00:01:01.824
And if he or she does it rightly,

00:01:01.664 --> 00:01:04.160
They cannot do it carelessly.

00:01:05.024 --> 00:01:08.288
The first thing when he awakes he asks

00:01:08.128 --> 00:01:10.336
How is the work prospering?

00:01:10.848 --> 00:01:13.408
And the last thought at night is:

00:01:13.440 --> 00:01:16.416
What can I do to fulfil my calling?

00:01:17.248 --> 00:01:21.728
Sometimes the anxiety even troubles her dreams.

00:01:21.696 --> 00:01:24.000
And she sighs, "O Lord!

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:26.400
Send now prosperity.

00:01:27.328 --> 00:01:31.776
How is the garden prospering which we are set to tend?

00:01:32.096 --> 00:01:34.048
Are we broken-hearted?

00:01:34.144 --> 00:01:36.640
Because nothing appears to flourish.

00:01:37.152 --> 00:01:39.040
Is it a bad season?

00:01:39.872 --> 00:01:42.944
Or is the soil lean and hungry?

00:01:43.840 --> 00:01:46.176
It is a very blessed relief.

00:01:46.336 --> 00:01:48.352
To an excess of care

00:01:48.448 --> 00:01:52.960
If we can fall into the habit of supposing him to be the gardener.

00:01:53.632 --> 00:01:57.696
If Jesus be the master and Lord in all things,

00:01:58.048 --> 00:02:01.344
It is not mine to keep all the church in order.

00:02:01.664 --> 00:02:05.696
I am not responsible for the growth of every Christian.

00:02:05.888 --> 00:02:08.800
Not for every backslider's errors.

00:02:08.896 --> 00:02:12.320
Nor for every professor's faults of life.

00:02:12.864 --> 00:02:15.872
This burden must not lie on me.

00:02:15.392 --> 00:02:18.112
He said, so that I shall be crushed by it.

00:02:18.848 --> 00:02:25.152
Supposing him to be the gardener then, the church enjoys a better oversight than mine.

00:02:25.280 --> 00:02:31.680
Better care is taken of the garden than could be taken by the most vigilant watchers.

00:02:31.680 --> 00:02:33.536
Even though by night.

00:02:33.312 --> 00:02:35.392
The frost devoured them.

00:02:35.296 --> 00:02:37.248
And by day the heat

00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:39.648
Supposing him?

00:02:39.808 --> 00:02:41.472
To be the gardener.

00:02:41.600 --> 00:02:44.800
Then all must go well in the long run.

00:02:46.016 --> 00:02:48.064
He that keeps Israel

00:02:47.936 --> 00:02:50.400
Doth neither slumber nor sleep,

00:02:51.136 --> 00:02:53.824
We need not fret and despond.

00:02:55.200 --> 00:02:59.584
I beg you, earnest workers, who are becoming depressed.

00:02:59.744 --> 00:03:01.856
To think this out a little.

00:03:03.040 --> 00:03:04.032
You see

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:07.328
It is yours to work under the Lord Jesus.

00:03:07.520 --> 00:03:11.584
But it is not yours to take the anxiety of his office.

00:03:11.456 --> 00:03:13.216
Into your souls.

00:03:13.120 --> 00:03:15.904
As though you were to bear his burdens.

00:03:16.544 --> 00:03:18.336
The undergardener

00:03:18.240 --> 00:03:24.608
The workman in the garden needs not fret about the whole garden as though it were all left to him.

00:03:24.608 --> 00:03:25.952
No, no.

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:29.440
Let him not take too much upon himself.

00:03:29.856 --> 00:03:34.688
I pray you, ease your anxiety by the fact of the case.

00:03:35.008 --> 00:03:38.016
So you have a number of young people around you?

00:03:37.824 --> 00:03:40.352
And you are watching for their souls.

00:03:40.704 --> 00:03:42.912
As they that must give account,

00:03:43.392 --> 00:03:44.736
This is well.

00:03:45.024 --> 00:03:47.424
But do not be worried and wearied.

00:03:47.584 --> 00:03:52.672
For after all the saving and the keeping of those souls is not in your hands.

00:03:52.672 --> 00:03:56.352
But it rests with one far more able than yourself.

00:03:57.184 --> 00:04:00.512
Just think that the Lord is the gardener.

00:04:01.248 --> 00:04:02.816
I know it is so.

00:04:02.592 --> 00:04:04.640
In matters of providence.

00:04:05.472 --> 00:04:08.512
A certain man of God in troublous times,

00:04:08.384 --> 00:04:12.768
Became quite unable to do his duty because he laid to heart.

00:04:12.672 --> 00:04:15.296
So much the ills of the age,

00:04:15.424 --> 00:04:18.560
He became depressed and disturbed.

00:04:18.752 --> 00:04:22.464
And he went on board a vessel wanting to leave the country.

00:04:22.240 --> 00:04:24.704
Which was getting into such a state,

00:04:24.544 --> 00:04:26.848
That he could no longer endure it.

00:04:27.360 --> 00:04:29.152
Then one said to him,

00:04:29.056 --> 00:04:30.528
Mr. Whitelock,

00:04:30.944 --> 00:04:33.216
Are you the manager of the world?

00:04:33.504 --> 00:04:34.528
No.

00:04:34.528 --> 00:04:36.384
He was not quite that.

00:04:36.864 --> 00:04:41.088
Did not God get on pretty well with it before you were born?

00:04:41.536 --> 00:04:45.248
And don't you think he will do very well with it when you are dead?

00:04:46.208 --> 00:04:47.968
That reflection.

00:04:47.968 --> 00:04:50.848
Helped to relieve the good man's mind.

00:04:50.944 --> 00:04:53.728
And he went back to do his duty.

00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:57.184
I want you thus to perceive

00:04:57.088 --> 00:04:59.424
The limit of your responsibility.

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:02.592
You are not the gardener himself.

00:05:02.656 --> 00:05:05.504
You are only one of the gardener's boys.

00:05:05.440 --> 00:05:07.776
Set to run on errands.

00:05:07.648 --> 00:05:09.568
Or to do a bit of digging.

00:05:09.536 --> 00:05:11.744
Or to sweep the paths?

00:05:12.416 --> 00:05:17.504
The garden is well enough managed, even though you are not head manager in it.

00:05:20.032 --> 00:05:22.592
While this relieves us of anxiety,

00:05:22.464 --> 00:05:30.912
It makes labour for Christ very sweet, because if the garden does not seem to repay us for our trouble, we say to ourselves,

00:05:30.784 --> 00:05:33.408
It is not my garden after all.

00:05:33.792 --> 00:05:36.512
Supposing him to be the gardener,

00:05:36.480 --> 00:05:40.064
I am quite willing to work on a barren piece of rock.

00:05:40.224 --> 00:05:42.944
Or tie up an old withered bough.

00:05:43.072 --> 00:05:45.280
Or dig a worthless sod?

00:05:45.664 --> 00:05:48.608
For if it only pleases Jesus,

00:05:48.672 --> 00:05:51.744
The work is for that one sole reason.

00:05:51.712 --> 00:05:54.304
Profitable to the last degree.

00:05:55.200 --> 00:05:59.104
It is not mine to question the wisdom of my task.

00:05:59.360 --> 00:06:01.024
But to set about it.

00:06:00.960 --> 00:06:03.680
In the name of my master and lord.

00:06:04.576 --> 00:06:07.392
Supposing him to be the gardener,

00:06:07.136 --> 00:06:11.072
Lifts the ponderous responsibility of it from me.

00:06:11.264 --> 00:06:12.608
And my work?

00:06:12.448 --> 00:06:15.200
Becomes pleasant and delightful

00:06:15.968 --> 00:06:19.232
In dealing with the souls of men and women,

00:06:19.264 --> 00:06:22.848
We meet with cases which are extremely difficult.

00:06:23.424 --> 00:06:26.176
Some persons are so timid

00:06:26.016 --> 00:06:27.424
And fearful

00:06:27.360 --> 00:06:29.888
That you do not know how to comfort them

00:06:30.528 --> 00:06:32.640
Others are so fast.

00:06:32.544 --> 00:06:36.416
And presumptuous that you hardly know how to help them.

00:06:36.864 --> 00:06:39.296
A few are so double-faced.

00:06:39.168 --> 00:06:41.408
That you cannot understand them.

00:06:41.664 --> 00:06:43.776
And others so fickle,

00:06:43.680 --> 00:06:45.504
That you cannot hold them.

00:06:46.624 --> 00:06:49.952
Some flowers puzzle the ordinary gardener.

00:06:50.624 --> 00:06:52.576
We meet with plants

00:06:52.448 --> 00:06:54.816
Which are covered with prickles.

00:06:55.104 --> 00:06:57.408
And when you try to train them,

00:06:57.184 --> 00:07:00.000
They wound the hand that would help them.

00:07:01.088 --> 00:07:03.040
These strange growths

00:07:02.816 --> 00:07:06.720
Would make a great model for you if you were the gardener.

00:07:07.392 --> 00:07:10.304
But supposing him to be the gardener,

00:07:10.624 --> 00:07:16.032
You have the happiness of being able to go to him constantly, saying, Good Lord!

00:07:16.096 --> 00:07:19.232
I do not understand this singular creature

00:07:18.976 --> 00:07:22.464
It is as odd a plant as I am myself.

00:07:22.688 --> 00:07:25.888
Oh, that you would manage it, or tell me how.

00:07:26.592 --> 00:07:27.840
I have come.

00:07:27.680 --> 00:07:29.440
To seek your counsel.

00:07:31.232 --> 00:07:33.728
Constantly our trouble is

00:07:33.664 --> 00:07:36.608
That we have so many plants to look after.

00:07:36.608 --> 00:07:40.992
That we have not time to cultivate any one in the best manner.

00:07:41.376 --> 00:07:45.600
Because we have 50 more all wanting attention at the time.

00:07:45.888 --> 00:07:49.024
And then before we've done with the watering pot

00:07:48.864 --> 00:07:53.120
We have to fetch the hoe and the rake and the spade.

00:07:52.992 --> 00:07:56.096
And we are puzzled with these multiple cares.

00:07:55.840 --> 00:07:58.400
Even as Paul was when he said,

00:07:58.272 --> 00:08:01.216
That which cometh upon me daily,

00:08:01.376 --> 00:08:04.032
The care of all the churches.

00:08:04.896 --> 00:08:06.144
Ah, then.

00:08:06.016 --> 00:08:07.712
It's a blessed thing.

00:08:07.584 --> 00:08:12.352
to do the little we can do and leave the rest to Jesus.

00:08:12.384 --> 00:08:14.816
Supposing him to be the gardener?

00:08:16.800 --> 00:08:18.528
In the Church of God,

00:08:18.464 --> 00:08:20.256
There is a discipline

00:08:19.968 --> 00:08:22.144
Which we cannot exercise.

00:08:23.008 --> 00:08:27.712
I do not think it is half so hard to exercise discipline

00:08:27.488 --> 00:08:30.528
As it is not to be able to exercise it.

00:08:30.688 --> 00:08:33.472
When yet you feel that it ought to be done.

00:08:34.176 --> 00:08:37.536
The servants of the householder were perplexed.

00:08:37.376 --> 00:08:40.128
When they might not root up the tares.

00:08:40.576 --> 00:08:43.872
Didst thou not sow good seed in thy field?

00:08:43.744 --> 00:08:46.272
From whence then hath it tares,

00:08:46.304 --> 00:08:48.480
An enemy hath done this.

00:08:48.704 --> 00:08:51.872
Wilt thou then that we go and gather them up?

00:08:52.512 --> 00:08:54.432
Not so, said he.

00:08:54.784 --> 00:08:57.472
Lest ye root up the wheat with them.

00:08:58.432 --> 00:09:04.640
This afflicts the Christian minister when he must not remove a pestilent hindering weed.

00:09:05.120 --> 00:09:06.112
Yes.

00:09:05.888 --> 00:09:07.584
But supposing him,

00:09:07.520 --> 00:09:09.088
To be the gardener.

00:09:09.344 --> 00:09:12.288
And it is his will to let the weed remain.

00:09:12.672 --> 00:09:16.160
What have you and I to do but to hold our peace?

00:09:17.184 --> 00:09:21.472
He has a discipline more sure and safe than ours.

00:09:21.568 --> 00:09:24.352
And in due time the tares shall know it.

00:09:24.896 --> 00:09:28.608
In patience let us possess our souls.

00:09:30.432 --> 00:09:31.776
And then again,

00:09:31.808 --> 00:09:34.688
There is that succession in the garden.

00:09:34.496 --> 00:09:36.416
Which we cannot keep up.

00:09:37.280 --> 00:09:39.392
Plants will die down

00:09:39.296 --> 00:09:44.032
And others must be put into their places, or the garden will grow bare.

00:09:44.320 --> 00:09:48.032
But we know not where to find these fresh flowers.

00:09:48.256 --> 00:09:51.296
We say when yonder good man dies,

00:09:51.072 --> 00:09:52.768
Who will succeed him?

00:09:53.504 --> 00:09:56.416
That is a question I have heard many a time.

00:09:56.576 --> 00:09:58.624
Till I am rather weary of it.

00:09:59.072 --> 00:10:01.312
Who is to follow such a man?

00:10:02.208 --> 00:10:04.704
Let us wait till he is gone.

00:10:04.768 --> 00:10:06.464
And needs following.

00:10:06.880 --> 00:10:10.208
Why sell the man's coat when he can wear it himself?

00:10:11.232 --> 00:10:15.904
We are apt to think that when this race of good brethren shall die out,

00:10:15.744 --> 00:10:20.288
That none will arise worthy to unloose the latchets of their shoes.

00:10:20.672 --> 00:10:21.984
Well, friend,

00:10:21.952 --> 00:10:26.528
I could suppose a great many things but this morning my text is

00:10:26.368 --> 00:10:28.096
Supposing him?

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:29.536
To be the gardener.

00:10:29.824 --> 00:10:31.648
And on that supposition,

00:10:31.808 --> 00:10:36.192
I expect that the Lord has other plants in reserve

00:10:36.032 --> 00:10:38.080
Would you have not yet seen?

00:10:38.208 --> 00:10:41.728
And these will exactly fit into our places.

00:10:41.472 --> 00:10:43.168
When they become empty.

00:10:43.168 --> 00:10:45.152
And the Lord will keep up

00:10:44.928 --> 00:10:47.872
The true apostolical succession

00:10:47.968 --> 00:10:50.400
Till the day of his second advent.

00:10:51.168 --> 00:10:57.504
In every time of darkness and dismay, when the heart sinks and the spirits decline,

00:10:57.504 --> 00:11:00.672
And we think it is all over with the Church of God.

00:11:00.800 --> 00:11:03.168
Let us fall back on this.

00:11:03.296 --> 00:11:05.056
Supposing him,

00:11:05.024 --> 00:11:06.656
To be the gardener,

00:11:06.944 --> 00:11:11.648
And expect to see greater and better things than these.

00:11:12.672 --> 00:11:15.040
We are at the end of our wits.

00:11:15.424 --> 00:11:18.400
But he is not at the beginning of his yet.

00:11:19.168 --> 00:11:20.992
We are nonplussed.

00:11:21.472 --> 00:11:23.296
But he never will be.

00:11:24.128 --> 00:11:25.856
Therefore let us wait,

00:11:25.824 --> 00:11:27.392
And be tranquil

00:11:27.392 --> 00:11:30.208
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:11:31.424 --> 00:11:32.640
Fourthly,,

00:11:32.512 --> 00:11:37.376
I want you to notice that this supposition will give you a deliverance

00:11:37.184 --> 00:11:39.648
From many gloomy fears.

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:42.304
I walked down the garden.

00:11:42.176 --> 00:11:48.704
And I saw a place where all the path was strewn with leaves and broken branches and stones.

00:11:49.152 --> 00:11:52.736
And I saw the earth upon the flower-beds tossed about,

00:11:52.608 --> 00:11:56.896
And brutes lying quite out of the ground, all was in disorder.

00:11:57.504 --> 00:12:00.032
Had a dog been amusing himself?

00:11:59.968 --> 00:12:02.880
Or had a mischievous child been at work?

00:12:03.104 --> 00:12:05.184
If so, it was a great pity.

00:12:05.376 --> 00:12:06.464
But no,

00:12:06.624 --> 00:12:09.792
In a minute or two, I saw the gardener come back.

00:12:09.568 --> 00:12:13.856
And I perceived that he had been making all this disarrangement.

00:12:13.952 --> 00:12:20.800
He had been cutting and digging and hacking and mess making, and all for the good of the garden.

00:12:21.376 --> 00:12:24.032
It may be it has happened to some of you.

00:12:24.160 --> 00:12:27.520
That you have been a good deal clipped lately.

00:12:27.488 --> 00:12:33.248
And in your domestic affairs things have not been in so fair a state as you would have wished.

00:12:33.536 --> 00:12:35.552
It may be in the church.

00:12:35.328 --> 00:12:38.208
We have seen ill weeds plucked up.

00:12:38.336 --> 00:12:40.640
And the barren branches lopped,

00:12:40.576 --> 00:12:43.680
So that everything is on Deza B.

00:12:44.288 --> 00:12:46.656
Well, if the Lord has done it,

00:12:46.560 --> 00:12:48.960
Our gloomy fears are idle.

00:12:49.056 --> 00:12:52.800
Supposing him to be the gardener, all is well.

00:12:53.632 --> 00:12:59.968
As I was talking this over with my friend, I said to him, supposing him to be the gardener,

00:12:59.776 --> 00:13:03.008
Then the serpent will have a bad time of it.

00:13:03.552 --> 00:13:06.400
Supposing Adam to be the gardener?

00:13:06.240 --> 00:13:10.016
Then the serpent gets in, and mischief comes of it.

00:13:10.304 --> 00:13:13.312
But supposing Jesus to be the gardener,

00:13:13.440 --> 00:13:15.584
Woe to thee, serpent,

00:13:15.456 --> 00:13:18.816
There's a blow for thy head within half a minute.

00:13:18.656 --> 00:13:22.048
If thou dost but show thyself within the boundary.

00:13:22.592 --> 00:13:26.304
So if we are afraid that the devil should get in among us,

00:13:26.304 --> 00:13:32.256
Let us always in prayer entreat that there may be no space for the devil.

00:13:32.608 --> 00:13:36.032
Because the Lord Jesus Christ fills all.

00:13:36.064 --> 00:13:38.432
And keeps out the adversary.

00:13:39.232 --> 00:13:43.648
Other creatures besides serpents intrude into gardens.

00:13:43.456 --> 00:13:44.864
Caterpillars,

00:13:44.704 --> 00:13:46.624
And Palmer worms.

00:13:46.496 --> 00:13:51.616
And all sorts of destroying creatures are apt to devour our churches.

00:13:52.320 --> 00:13:54.112
How can we keep them out?

00:13:54.656 --> 00:13:57.504
The highest wall cannot exclude them.

00:13:57.312 --> 00:14:01.248
There is no protection except one, and that is...

00:14:01.152 --> 00:14:02.912
Supposing him,

00:14:02.752 --> 00:14:04.256
To be the gardener.

00:14:04.832 --> 00:14:06.464
Thus it is written:

00:14:06.368 --> 00:14:09.888
I will rebuke the devourer for your sakes.

00:14:09.760 --> 00:14:13.408
And he shall not destroy the fruits of your ground.

00:14:13.312 --> 00:14:19.936
Neither shall your vine cast her fruit before the time in the field, saith the Lord of hosts.

00:14:20.480 --> 00:14:27.456
Thank you for listening, friends. this podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

